ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.315                Enzyme
NAME        11-cis-retinol dehydrogenase;
            RDH5 (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     11-cis-retinol:NAD+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    11-cis-retinol---[retinal-binding-protein] + NAD+ = 11-cis-retinal---[retinol-binding-protein] + NADH + H+
ALL_REAC    (other) R03048 R08382
SUBSTRATE   11-cis-retinol---[retinal-binding-protein];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003]
PRODUCT     11-cis-retinal---[retinol-binding-protein];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     This enzyme, abundant in the retinal pigment epithelium, catalyses the reduction of 11-cis-retinol to 11-cis-retinal [1] while the substrate is bound to the retinal-binding protein [4]. This is a crucial step in the regeneration of 11-cis-retinal, the chromophore of rhodopsin. The enzyme can also accept other cis forms of retinol [2].
